lead_paragraph: The Royal Mail steamship Canada, Captain HARRISON, with 71 through passengers, arrived at her wharf at 7o'clock this morning. The English news is devoid of interest. The Overland mail reached London on the 18th Sept., by express, with Calcutta advices to August 7th.

snippet: MY DEAR MR. GRINNELL: I write to you in much agitation and confusion of mind, which you will not wonder at, when you hear that Capt. Penny, with his two ships, has returned, and announces the approaching return of Capt. Austin's squadron, after being...
lead_paragraph: MY DEAR MR. GRINNELL: I write to you in much agitation and confusion of mind, which you will not wonder at, when you hear that Capt. Penny, with his two ships, has returned, and announces the approaching return of Capt. Austin's squadron, after being out for only half the period for which they were equipped.
headline: {"main"=>"Letter from Lady Franklin to Mr. Grinnell."}

snippet: The Journal of Commerce published the following letter, remarking that 'the writer having formerly occupied the post of Ambassador to the Courts of London and Paris, his remarks on the subject of an alleged treaty between France and England,...
lead_paragraph: The Journal of Commerce published the following letter, remarking that 'the writer having formerly occupied the post of Ambassador to the Courts of London and Paris, his remarks on the subject of an alleged treaty between France and England, guaranteeing to Spain the possession of Cuba, will be read with interest." This statement,
abstract: Letter of Andw. Stephenson on the European view
headline: {"main"=>"The Cuban Question in Europe--Letter from Ex-Minister Stevenson."}

snippet: Any one who comes to Munich with the purpose of seeing all its works of art, should take lodging by the quarter. The passing traveler who attempts fulfil such a purpose in a week, will only weary his eyes and carry away a confused remembrance of...
lead_paragraph: Any one who comes to Munich with the purpose of seeing all its works of art, should take lodging by the quarter. The passing traveler who attempts fulfil such a purpose in a week, will only weary his eyes and carry away a confused remembrance of forms, colors, and artistic names.
headline: {"main"=>"SKETCHES OF EUROPE.; Munich--its Galleries of Art--Statutes--Streets, Theatres, &c.", "kicker"=>"1"}

snippet: The Queen returned from Ischl, yesterday and proceeded to Potedam. The Duchess of Orleans will stay one or two months at Eisenach.
lead_paragraph: The Queen returned from Ischl, yesterday and proceeded to Potedam. The Duchess of Orleans will stay one or two months at Eisenach.
